From 7cf7daa5d78ba32e2170435123d8c9c5a753b8f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Chuah, Kim Tatt" <kim.tatt.chuah@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 26 Jun 2018 06:14:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 02/58] net: stmmac: Add support for HW-accelerated VLAN
 stripping

Currently, VLAN tag stripping is done by driver in stmmac_rx_vlan().
Add support for VLAN tag stripping by the MAC hardware for MAC drivers
that support it. This is done by adding rx_hw_van() and set_hw_vlan_mode()
callbacks at stmmac_ops struct which are called if registered by the MAC
driver.

Signed-off-by: Chuah, Kim Tatt <kim.tatt.chuah@intel.com>
[Fixed Fix missing netdev->features assignment in stmmac_set_features.
 Ported changes to generic HW Interface helpers design. - OBL]
Signed-off-by: Ong Boon Leong <boon.leong.ong@intel.com>

Change-Id: I759d7eb848d85b589e11fe3b0b80b8e771ee0df6
